 04/bat.jpg
UID:-r40DVSTwPpankLwGnMGu
SUMMARY:Buffalo Bayou Cruise: Bats
DTSTAMP:20260618T030750Z
DTSTART:20260703T192000Z
DESCRIPTION:Sail the scenic waterway on a 90-minute\, guided tour from down
	town to Waugh Drive Bridge and back to watch the emergence of the 250\,000
	+ Mexican free-tailed bats that live under the bridge. \nOur knowledgeable
	 guide will share details about the bats’ eating patterns\, behavior and c
	ontributions to the bayou’s ecosystem. Space is limited\, and boat tours f
	ill up fast. Boat departs 45 minutes before sunset. \nCost\nStarting at $3
	0/person \nDuration\n90 minutes \nDeparture location\n Allen’s Landing (10
	19 Commerce St.) \nPlease note\, children must be at least four years old 
	to board the pontoon boat. \n  \nPURCHASE TICKETS\n\nhttps://buffalobayou.
	org/event/july-2026-buffalo-bayou-cruise-bats-48/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou Pa
	rtnership
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/july-2026-buffalo-bayou-cruise-bats-48/
LOCATION:ALLEN’S LANDING\, 1001 Commerce Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, Un
	ited States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:buffalo-bayou-partnership
CATEGORIES:Buffalo Bayou Partnership
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/w
 p-content/uploads/2023/04/Waugh-Bridge-Bat-Colony-1-1.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/
 04/Waugh-Bridge-Bat-Colony-1-1.jpg
UID:ulzW0jRffTpMCjGpSnXRs
SUMMARY:Bat Chat
DTSTAMP:20260618T030750Z
DTSTART:20260703T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Stroll to Waugh Drive Bridge for a Bat Chat with the Houston Ar
	ea Bat Team and see the bat colony up close! \nDid you know? These populat
	ion of Mexican Free-tailed Bats at the Waugh Bridge can reach a peak of ap
	proximately 300\,000 in the summer months! Around sunset\, the colony leav
	es the crevices beneath the bridge and create a whirlwind-like formation a
	s they emerge. Join the Houston Area Bat Team to learn and discover as the
	y share fun\, educational facts and insights about these miniature\, flyin
	g mammals! \nInvite your family and friends\, bring a picnic blanket\, wea
	r your bug spray\, and admire this unique phenomena. \n\n\n\nBat Chats are
	 held every Friday evening from May to August as part of our Summer Specie
	s series\, starting 30 minutes before sunset. \n  \nCost\nFree \nTime\n7:3
	0 – 8:30pm (30 minutes before sunset) \nMeeting Location\nWaugh Bridge Bat
	 Colony Observation Deck (along Allen Parkway) \nFREE REGISTRATION\n\nhttp
	s://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-july-bat-chat/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou Partn
	ership
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-july-bat-chat/
LOCATION:Waugh Drive Bat Bridge\, 1
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:buffalo-bayou-partnership
CATEGORIES:Buffalo Bayou Partnership
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
